==Armour==
'''Rune armour''' is the highest-quality non-degradable [[armour]] that [[free-to-play]] players can wear, and the second-highest quality armour on the standard metallic armour spectrum ([[Bronze equipment#Armour|bronze]] to [[Dragon equipment#Armour|dragon]]). Rune armour requires 40 [[Defence]] to wear and [[Dragon Slayer I]] to wear the [[rune platebody]], but only 40 Defence to wear all other pieces (thus, Dragon Slayer I need not be completed). With a full set costing around {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Rune armour set (lg)}}}} [[coins]], the armour provides excellent Defence for its price, making it the best choice for warriors with level 40 Defence.

{{Infotable Bonuses|Rune med helm|Rune full helm|Rune chainbody|Rune platebody|Rune platelegs|Rune plateskirt|Rune sq shield|Rune kiteshield|Rune boots|Rune gloves|Rune defender#Normal|sort=dslash|nototals=yes}}

==Other==
Ornamental rune armour, such as [[Rune heraldic armour|heraldic]], [[Rune trimmed armour|trimmed]], [[Rune god armour|god armour]], and [[gilded armour]] have the same bonuses as standard rune armour, with the addition of a +1 [[prayer bonus]] on god armour, and the exception of the ranged attack bonus of the god and trimmed variants of the kiteshield being -2 rather than -3. These can be obtained from the member's only [[Treasure Trails]] minigame. These armour sets are often worn by more wealthy players due to their looks and price.

'''Note:''' Other players '''''cannot''''' trim or bless armour. Players claiming to do so are [[scammer]]s.
